{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Insert simmering basket into mixing bowl and weigh lentils into it. Remove simmering basket with aid of spatula and rinse lentils until water runs clear.","Place lentils, water, salt, turmeric and pandan leaf into mixing bowl and cook <nobr>12 min\/100°C\/\/speed <\/nobr>.","Add coconut cream and heat <nobr>3 min\/80°C\/\/speed <\/nobr>. Transfer into a thermal serving bowl or other large bowl and cover to keep warm. Clean and dry mixing bowl.","Place oil into mixing bowl and heat <nobr>1 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<\/nobr>, then continue heating <nobr>1 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<\/nobr>, adding spices separately through hole in mixing bowl lid starting with mustard seeds.","Add onion, garlic and chillies and chop <nobr>4 sec\/speed 4<\/nobr>.","Add curry leaves and sauté <nobr>2 min\/Varoma\/\/speed 2<\/nobr>.","Add tomato and cook <nobr>2 min\/Varoma\/\/speed 2<\/nobr>. Pour mixture over cooked dahl and stir to combine. Serve warm."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["200 g red lentils","500 g water","1 tsp salt","1 tsp ground turmeric","1 pandan leaf, tied into a knot","60 g coconut cream","60 g oil","½ tsp black mustard seeds","½ tsp cumin seeds","½ tsp fenugreek seeds","1 red onion, cut into halves","1 garlic clove","2 fresh bird's eye chillies (green or red), deseeded if preferred","1 sprig fresh curry leaves","1 fresh tomato, cut into cubes (1 cm)"]}],"id":"r115166","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-zaMTogRznRs\/XZVQO1PzGfI\/AAAAAAAAc_A\/H9IVVgqDPJYvQEFWXKSGu5bx1pGQfj7oACLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_J7MbsZAzt8xYWx3K.png","title":"Lentil curry (dahl)","publishedAt":"2016-07-17T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"9.6 g","fat":"13 g","uom":"per 1 portions","carbohydrates":"20.5 g","calories":"1034 kJ \/ 246 kcal"},"usefulItems":"thermal serving bowl or other large bowl","hintsAndTricks":["Serve curry with steamed rice, Pittu (refer to the Pittu recipe in this collection) or Coconut roti (refer to the Kuruma iraichchi recipe in this collection).","You can find black mustard seeds and fenugreek seeds at spice shops or online."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","30m","6 portions"]}